Sentencas: The Y1-xBaCoCuO5+delta (x = 0.00, 0.03, 0.05, 0.07, 0.10) oxides with different Y3+-deficiency were studied as cathodes for solid oxide fuel cell.
Titulo: The evolution of structure and electrochemical properties of Y-site deficiency Y1-xBaCoCuO5+δ cathode for solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: XRD results show that Y1-xBaCoCuO5+delta oxide exhibits orthorhombic structure, which displays a lattice expansion with increasing Y3+-deficiency.
Titulo: The evolution of structure and electrochemical properties of Y-site deficiency Y1-xBaCoCuO5+δ cathode for solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The oxygen content decreases gradually with increased x.
Titulo: The evolution of structure and electrochemical properties of Y-site deficiency Y1-xBaCoCuO5+δ cathode for solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The electrical conductivity reduces with increased Y-deficiency x from 0.00 to 0.10 and all samples exhibit a typical semiconducting behavior.
Titulo: The evolution of structure and electrochemical properties of Y-site deficiency Y1-xBaCoCuO5+δ cathode for solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The average expansion coefficients of Y1-x-BaCoCuO5+delta are 12.24-14.21 x 10-6 K-1 for x = 0.00 to 0.10 samples, which shows a slightly increase with the higher Y-deficiency content.
Titulo: The evolution of structure and electrochemical properties of Y-site deficiency Y1-xBaCoCuO5+δ cathode for solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The results of impedance spectra indicate that introducing Y3+-deficiency reduces the polarization resistance (Rp).
Titulo: The evolution of structure and electrochemical properties of Y-site deficiency Y1-xBaCoCuO5+δ cathode for solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The lowest Rp value, typically from 0.029 U cm(2) at 800 degrees C to 0.133 U cm(2) at 650 degrees C, is obtained by x = 0.07 sample.
Titulo: The evolution of structure and electrochemical properties of Y-site deficiency Y1-xBaCoCuO5+δ cathode for solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: An electrolyte-supported single cell was fabricated and the peak power density of Y0.93BaCoCuO(5+delta) (x = 0.07) sample achieves 862, 643, 426, 274 and 152 mW cm-2 at 850, 800, 750, 700 and 650 degrees C, respectively.
Titulo: The evolution of structure and electrochemical properties of Y-site deficiency Y1-xBaCoCuO5+δ cathode for solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: Our finding demonstrates that the electrochemical per-formance of Y1-xBaCoCuO5+delta oxides can be significantly improved by introducing the Y3+-deficiency.
Titulo: The evolution of structure and electrochemical properties of Y-site deficiency Y1-xBaCoCuO5+δ cathode for solid oxide fuel cells
